Upstream source paths (as of the `blocksuite-main` reference checkout vendored
into the original Spectre monorepo at `reference/blocksuite-main` — see
PROVENANCE.md in this repo's root for the extraction commit):

  - packages/affine/blocks/surface/src/utils/priority-queue.ts
      -> priority-queue.ts (verbatim, MPL-2.0 header added)

  - packages/affine/blocks/surface/src/utils/graph.ts
      -> graph.ts (import paths adjusted to point at local gfx-types.ts;
         algorithm body unmodified)

  - packages/affine/blocks/surface/src/utils/a-star.ts
      -> a-star.ts (import paths adjusted to point at local graph.ts,
         priority-queue.ts, and gfx-types.ts; algorithm body unmodified)

  - packages/affine/gfx/connector/src/connector-manager.ts
      -> path-generator.ts (NOT verbatim: this file extracts only the pure,
         framework-free orthogonal path-generation logic — PathGenerator,
         computeOffset, computeNextStartEndpoint, getNextPoint,
         computeNextStartEndpoint, computePoints, getConnectablePoints,
         getDirectPath, mergePath, adjustStartEndPoint, and their private
         helpers — and ports them to plain TypeScript types. All Lit,
         @preact/signals-core, @blocksuite/std (GfxController/GfxModel),
         @blocksuite/affine-model, and rendering/overlay code (Overlay,
         ConnectionOverlay, canvas ctx rendering, anchors/selection UI) was
         removed. The ported algorithm functions retain their original
         control flow and math.)

  - gfx-types.ts (this file has no direct upstream counterpart): a minimal,
      dependency-free reimplementation of the handful of `@blocksuite/global/gfx`
      primitives that a-star.ts, graph.ts, and path-generator.ts need
      (IVec, IVec3, Bound, Vec, PointLocation, almostEqual, isOverlap,
      lineIntersects, linePolygonIntersects). Reimplemented from the public
      BlockSuite `@blocksuite/global` package
      (packages/framework/global/src/gfx/{math.ts,model/bound.ts,model/vec.ts,
      model/point-location.ts}) to drop the @blocksuite/* package dependency
      while preserving the exact same math/semantics used by the vendored
      files above.

  - packages/affine/gfx/pointer/src/snap/snap-overlay.ts
      -> snap-distribution.ts (NOT verbatim: labeled port, same convention as
         path-generator.ts. Extracts `SnapOverlay._alignDistributeHorizontally`,
         `_alignDistributeVertically`, and `_calculateClosestDistances` —
         the equal-spacing "distribution" snap search (evaluate every
         same-axis-crossing box pair for a "snap between"/"snap left of
         pair"/"snap right of pair" candidate center, keep the closest within
         threshold, then chain outward collecting further boxes at the exact
         same spacing) and the 9-way closest-alignment-distance search
         (center-center, center-edge x4, edge-edge x4 per axis). Rewritten
         against this repo's `{x, y, width, height}` bounds shape (upstream's
         `Bound` uses `w`/`h`) as plain functions, with `Overlay`/canvas-paint,
         `GfxController`/viewport/grid-search, and Mindmap/Connector
         model-type filtering removed (this repo's `snapping.ts` already owns
         candidate scoping and CanvasStage.tsx owns rendering). `ALIGN_THRESHOLD`
         (8), `DISTRIBUTION_LINE_OFFSET` (1), `STROKE_WIDTH` (2), and the two
         guide colors (`#8B5CF6` alignment / `#CC4187` distribution, plus the
         `10`-world-px end-tick bar) are copied verbatim from
         `snap-overlay.ts` lines 35-37 and 700/723-725. One documented
         deviation: `alignDistributeVertically` fixes two apparent upstream
         axis bugs in `_alignDistributeVertically` (sorting by `center[0]`
         instead of `center[1]`, comparing `db.maxY < ub.minX` instead of
         `ub.minY`) — see the file's header comment and inline note at the fix
         site for detail. Every other branch/formula is unchanged from
         upstream.

  - packages/affine/gfx/connector/src/connector-manager.ts (`getAnchors`,
    lines 133-159, and `ConnectionOverlay.renderConnector`'s decision cascade,
    lines 958-1061)
      -> ../../connection-overlay.ts (NOT verbatim: algorithm-only port.
         `getAnchors`' 4-cardinal-candidate -> center-to-candidate-line ->
         real-outline-intersection projection is reproduced as
         `getConnectionAnchors`, with rotation removed (this repo's object
         schema has no per-object rotation field) and
         `getLineIntersections`/`getNearestPoint` (upstream: per-shape-model
         methods) reimplemented locally as `polygonLineIntersection`/
         `nearestOutlinePoint` operating on a `CanvasPoint[]` outline polygon
         built per object type (`outlinePolygon`: true rect/pill/diamond/
         arrow-shape outlines, bounding-rect fallback for every other type —
         the same conservative fallback upstream uses for diamond/ellipse/
         triangle per its own `// FIXME` at `connector-manager.ts:975`).
         `renderConnector`'s 5-step decision cascade (anchor snap < 8 view-px
         -> outline snap < 8 world-px -> inside-shape -> next candidate ->
         free point) is reproduced as `resolveConnectionCascade`, with the
         canvas-paint half of `ConnectionOverlay` (the `render()` method,
         `_emphasisColor`/theme listening, `sourceBounds`/`targetBounds`
         highlight rects) omitted — this repo renders the overlay in React
         (CanvasStage.tsx) from this module's pure return values.
         `ANCHOR_OFFSET_PX` (10), `HOVER_HIT_EXPAND_PX` (10),
         `ANCHOR_SNAP_VIEW_PX` (8), and `OUTLINE_SNAP_WORLD_PX` (8) are copied
         verbatim from `connector-manager.ts` lines 135, 976, 1006, 1011.

